title: Noida’s ‘Jungle Trail’ to open in July; visitors can enjoy night safari

author: AMIT KUMAR
description: Dhruv Jurel's journey from a soldier's son to an Indian cricketer is inspiring. His father, a Kargil War veteran, initially opposed his cricket dream due to financial constraints, but his mother's sacrifice changed everything.
title: Dhruv Jurel: MS Dhoni’s admirer, Hanuman bhakt, son of a Kargil War hero

author: TNN
description: During an official inspection at Bijnor district hospital, a kidney patient died mid-dialysis due to a power cut and a non-functional generator lacking fuel. The private firm responsible for the dialysis unit is under scrutiny for negligence, with authorities seizing records and initiating legal action due to mismanagement and lack of cleanliness.
title: ‘Half his blood stuck in machine’: UP kidney patient dies during dialysis

author: TOI WORLD DESK
title: Iran-Israel conflict: Oil refinery, civilian areas; who struck what in latest escalation

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Australian batter Steve Smith sustained a finger injury during the World Test Championship Final, dislocating his right little finger while attempting a catch. Fortunately, surgery was avoided, and Smith remains hopeful of participating in the upcoming three-match Test series against the West Indies, commencing June 25.
title: 'Love-Hate relationship with Lord’s': Steve Smith reflects after WTC final loss

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: NASA is embarking on the Sporadic-E ElectroDynamics (SEED) mission, launching rockets from Kwajalein Atoll to investigate unpredictable Sporadic-E layers in the ionosphere. These layers disrupt radio signals, impacting communication and navigation systems. The mission aims to understand their formation and behavior near the magnetic equator, enhancing prediction models to mitigate signal interruptions.
title: NASA launching rockets to probe ionospheric clouds disrupting global communication

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Wayne Gretzky, a Canadian icon, faces backlash for his association with Donald Trump, particularly after Trump's remarks about Canada. Critics question Gretzky's Canadian identity, fueled by images of him at Trump events. Despite Gretzky's attempts to remain neutral, his silence on Trump's policies and his wife's social media activity have intensified the controversy, potentially impacting his legacy in Canada.
title: Wayne Gretzky caught in backlash; Trump calls him ‘a free agent’; Canadians question his loyalty

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Temba Bavuma led South Africa to a historic World Test Championship victory at Lord's, ending a 27-year title drought. Following a tense win against Australia, marked by Aiden Markram's century and Bavuma's resilience, the captain shared the momentous occasion with his son.
title: A beautiful celebration: Temba Bavuma’s walk with his son goes viral- watch

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Following the Air India plane crash, the Turkish government refuted claims that Turkish Technic maintained the Boeing 787-8 Dreamliner involved. Agreements between Air India and Turkish Technic, set for 2024-25, only cover maintenance for B777 aircraft, not the 787-8. Air India plans to reduce reliance on Turkish Technic amid strained relations.
title: AI plane crash: Turkey denies Dreamliner maintenance link; issues clarification

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Aiden Markram's remarkable 136 led South Africa to a historic five-wicket victory over Australia in the World Test Championship at Lord's, securing their first major ICC trophy since 1998. Markram's match-winning innings and resilience helped the team overcome past failures, especially after the T20 World Cup final defeat.
title: Aiden Markram shares the story of having a drink with fan at Lord's

author: RAUNAK BOSE
description: LeBron James has ignited retirement speculation with a cryptic social media post, leaving fans and the Lakers organization in suspense. After a remarkable 22nd season, James hints at uncertainty about his future, presenting the Lakers with a dilemma as they await his decision on his contract. Family considerations and legacy will heavily influence his choice.
title: Lakers star LeBron James Drops cryptic retirement hint—Is this the end of an era?

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Amidst escalating tensions and Israel's military offensive against Iran, Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu extended warm birthday wishes to President Donald Trump, lauding him as a steadfast ally. Trump voiced strong support for Israel's actions, deeming the strikes "excellent" and hinting at further consequences for Iran. As hostilities deepen, both sides brace for a potentially prolonged conflict.
title: 'Our enemy is your enemy': Netanyahu praises Trump on his birthday; posts a video message

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi has embarked on a three-nation tour, starting with Cyprus, to strengthen bilateral relations and explore cooperation in trade, investment, and technology. He will then attend the G7 Summit in Canada, addressing global issues and the priorities of the Global South.
title: PM Modi on foreign tour: Cyprus, Canada, Croatia on itinerary- his agenda

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: A shocking rift has reportedly emerged between Taylor Swift and Blake Lively, sending shockwaves through Hollywood. Sources suggest a deeply personal issue caused the fracture, impacting Swift's inner circle. Fans noticed Lively's absence from recent events, fueling speculation further. Lyrics from Swift's song 'Bejeweled' are now being interpreted as clues about the fallout.
title: Taylor Swift’s alleged falling out with Blake Lively gets deeper

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Across the United States, widespread anti-Trump protests unfolded coinciding with President Trump's military parade in Washington, D.C., marking the Army's 250th anniversary. Demonstrations, organized under the banner "No Kings," criticized the administration's policies. Tensions flared in cities like Los Angeles and Phoenix, leading to clashes and arrests.
title: Massive military parade in DC, 'No Kings' protests sweep US - how day unfolded

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Following Israel's strike on Iran's nuclear facility, tensions have escalated dramatically. Israel launched a major counteroffensive targeting Tehran's defense and energy infrastructure, prompting retaliatory missile strikes from Iran that resulted in casualties in northern Israel. The conflict has led to the cancellation of nuclear negotiations and raised global concerns about a wider regional war, with calls for de-escalation.
title: Nuclear sites hit, oil depot targeted: Israel-Iran trade heavy blows; key details

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: A helicopter carrying seven individuals crashed in a remote area of Uttarakhand on Sunday. The aircraft, which had just dropped pilgrims at the Kedarnath shrine, was en route to Gaurikund when it disappeared between Trijuginarayan and Gaurikund in Rudraprayag district. Inspector General Rajiv Swaroop confirmed the crash, noting the challenging location.
title: Uttarakhand: Helicopter flying to Kedarnath crashes near Gaurikund; 6 were on board

author: SHOEB KHAN
description: Shrawan Kumar, a 19-year-old from a humble background in Balotra, has cleared NEET, securing a remarkable rank despite working in a factory and his parents washing dishes for a living. Access to electricity and a smartphone significantly aided his studies, enabling him to receive free NEET coaching from government doctors.
title: Rajasthan factory worker, son of utensil cleaner, cracks NEET

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Dozens missing, homes torched, and hundreds wounded in overnight massacre in Benue state; rights group and police confirm attack
title: Gunmen kill at least 100 in north-central Nigeria village attack, says Amnesty

author: TOI NEWS DESK
title: Relief from heat in Delhi: Rains lash city; waterlogging slows traffic

author: KRISHNA CHAUDHARY
description: In Baghpat's Budhpur village, thirteen deaths in the last 15 days are raising concerns about water contamination from industrial waste. Locals attribute the fatalities, mainly from heart issues and kidney failure, to polluted groundwater. Officials have acknowledged the issue, prompting medical screenings and calls for accountability from pollution control bodies.
title: 13 dead in 15 days as 'toxic drain' sparks health crisis in UP village

author: NASEER GANAI
description: Lieutenant Governor Manoj Sinha announced the reopening of 16 tourist destinations in Jammu and Kashmir, out of the 48 closed after the Pahalgam terror attack. Eight destinations in the Valley and eight in Jammu will reopen from June 17, following appeals from political leaders and tourism stakeholders. The decision aims to restore normalcy, with further reopenings planned after security assessments.
title: After April 22 terror attack, 16 Jammu & Kashmir's tourist spots reopen

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Father's Day, celebrated globally on the third Sunday of June, honors fathers and father figures for their guidance and love. Originating in the US in the early 20th century, Sonora Smart Dodd championed the holiday, officially recognized in 1972. Celebrations vary across cultures, emphasizing family time and appreciation.
title: Happy father's day: 75+ messages, greetings, wishes, and quotes

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A senior Israeli official hinted that Ayatollah Ali Khamenei could be targeted as Israel intensifies its campaign against Iranian nuclear and military infrastructure. This marks a shift towards potentially dismantling Iran's leadership. Recent strikes, including at Natanz, have reportedly inflicted substantial damage, while Iran retaliates with missile attacks, escalating regional tensions and raising global concerns.
title: Khamenei 'not off limits': Israel ups the ante; Iran conflict enters new phase

author: SUPARNA ROY
description: Mahesh Kumar from Rajasthan, a Hindi-medium student, defied expectations by topping NEET-UG 2025 with a 99.9 percentile score. Initially hesitant to pursue science due to language concerns, Mahesh overcame self-doubt with hard work and determination. His family revealed his initial inclination towards humanities, but his sister's encouragement led him to medicine.
title: Rajasthan boy overcomes self-doubt to script NEET success story

author: ANJALI SINGH
description: Haryana's Super 100 program is transforming the lives of underprivileged students by providing them with quality education and coaching for competitive exams. Manvi, once discouraged for being a girl, excelled in the program and secured a high-paying job after graduating from IIT Gandhinagar.
title: 'Another girl, abort her’: Haryana’s Super 100 saves daughters of state

author: TNN
description: Aryan Asari, a 17-year-old from Aravalli, was questioned by Ahmedabad police regarding a viral video of the Air India flight 171 crash. The video, showing the plane's descent and explosion, quickly spread online. Aryan, residing near the runway, stated he didn't film it but screen-recorded it from a friend before sharing it with his father.
title: Ahmedabad: Teen whose AI-171 crash video went viral questioned by cops, says clip was screen-recorded

author: ASHISH CHAUHAN
description: Yasmin Vora, along with her nephew Pervez and his young daughter Zuveriya, tragically perished in a plane crash en route to London for a family baby shower. Yasmin had changed her flight to accompany them, and Yasin, her husband, last spoke to her just before takeoff when she expressed concerns about the flight.
title: 'Non-functioning AC and feeling strange': AI crash victim’s last words to husband

author: TNN
description: In Assam's Dhubri, communal unrest erupted after cattle remains were found near temples during Eid. Authorities imposed shoot-on-sight orders at night and arrested 38 individuals. Chief Minister Sarma, after visiting Dhubri, reported the discovery of secessionist group posters advocating for merger with Bangladesh.
title: Communal unrest: 38 arrested in Assam's Dhubri

author: TNN
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi is embarking on a three-nation tour, starting with Cyprus, marking the first visit by an Indian PM since 2002. He will then attend the G7 Summit in Canada, engaging in bilateral meetings, including a potential encounter with US President Trump.
title: PM Modi to begin 3-nation tour from Cyprus today

author: TNN
description: Following the recent Air India crash, the airline's Boeing 787 Dreamliner fleet is undergoing urgent safety checks as directed by the DGCA. The government has formed a high-level committee to investigate the crash and recommend aviation safety reforms, with a report due by September 13. Air India will provide interim compensation to the families of the deceased and the survivor.
title: Urgent checks on AI's 787 fleet: Aviation minister
